Magistrate Peter Dingwell said the assault launched by Burnell, from Canberra, was a serious offence and was a knee jerk reaction to comment made about a hair do.

'The reason he committed the offence remains a mystery,' Mr Dingwell said.

'It was a somewhat spur of the moment action, a disproportionate response to a jocular remark.'

The magistrate said he believed Burnell regretted his actions because he had entered a guilty plea, and due to his age and his previous criminal history, he did not think prison was an suitable punishment.

Burnell dodged prison time and was sentenced to a 12-month good behaviour order

